	<p class="cs709C557D"><span class="cs8498B7A6">WEST VIRGINIA LEGISLATURE</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 </span><span class="csC2FEE544">REGULAR SESSION</span><div style="width:49pt;height:32pt;border-width:0.5pt;border-style:solid;border-color:Black;background-color:#FFFFFF;margin:0pt 9pt 0pt 9pt;padding:5pt 0pt 0pt 0pt;">
		<p class="csAC81313F"><span class="csB9803513">FISCAL NOTE</span></p></div>
	</p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Introduced</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">House Bill 5583</span></p><p class="csFF933113"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Delegates Bell, Shamblin, Toney, Pritt, and Stephens</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Introduced February 16, 2026; referred to the Committee on Education]</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, by adding a new article, designated &sect;18-36-1, &sect;18-36-2, &sect;18-36-3, &sect;18-36-4, &sect;18-36-5, &sect;18-36-6, &sect;18-36-7, &sect;18-36-8, &sect;18-36-9, and &sect;18-36-10, relating to the creation of the West Virginia Seal of Civic Literacy Act; providing for a short title; setting forth legislative findings and purpose; providing for definitions; establishing the program; providing for administration and implementation; providing for recognition and use of the seal; setting forth rulemaking authority; providing for cost and funding; providing for severability; and providing for an effective date.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs456817A0">Article 36. West Virginia Seal of Civic Literacy Act.</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;18-36-1. Short Title. </span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">This article shall be known and may be cited as the &quot;West Virginia Seal of Civic Literacy Act.&quot; </span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;18-36-2. Legislative Findings and Purpose.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) Legislative Findings. - The Legislature finds that: </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) A constitutional republic depends upon an informed and civically literate citizenry capable of understanding the structure, principles, and responsibilities of government; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Civic knowledge promotes informed voting, peaceful civic participation, respect for the rule of law, and engagement in local, state, and national affairs; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) West Virginia already requires students to complete civics coursework and participate in a state-required civics assessment as a condition of graduation; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Recognizing exceptional achievement in civics education encourages academic excellence and signals the value of civic knowledge to students, families, postsecondary institutions, employers, and the broader community; and </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(5) Other academic seals and distinctions have proven effective in motivating student achievement and recognizing subject-matter mastery. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) Purpose. &nbsp;- The purpose of this article is to: </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Establish a formal Seal of Civic Literacy awarded to students who demonstrate exceptional mastery of civics; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Encourage deeper understanding of the United States Constitution, the Constitution of West Virginia, and the rights and responsibilities of citizenship; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Provide students with a meaningful academic distinction that may be used for postsecondary education, employment, scholarships, and civic recognition; and </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Promote civic education as a core component of public education in West Virginia. </span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;18-36-3. Definitions.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csF3C8A5A3">&nbsp;</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">For purposes of this article: </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) &quot;Department&quot; means the West Virginia Department of Education. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) &quot;State-required civics assessment&quot; means the civics examination required by the State of West Virginia for high school graduation, as established by statute or State Board of Education policy. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) &quot;Seal of Civic Literacy&quot; means an official recognition awarded by the State of West Virginia to a student who meets the requirements set forth in this article. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) &quot;Eligible student&quot; means a public high school student enrolled in a West Virginia public school or public charter school who has completed required civics coursework.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;18-36-4. Establishment of the Seal of Civic Literacy.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) There is hereby created the West Virginia Seal of Civic Literacy. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) The Seal of Civic Literacy shall be awarded to any eligible student who: </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Completes all state-required civics coursework; and </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Achieves one of the following: </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(A) A score of ninety percent (90%) or higher on the state-required civics assessment; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(B) A score of four &nbsp;or five on the Advanced Placement (AP) United States Government and Politics examination; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(C) A score of four or five on the Advanced Placement (AP) United States History examination; or </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(D) A final grade of 90% or higher in a dual credit United States History or United States Government course offered through an accredited institution of higher education. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) The Seal of Civic Literacy shall be: </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Affixed to the student&rsquo;s high school diploma or diploma supplement, transcript, or other official academic record, as determined by the Department; and </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Recognized as an official academic distinction of the State of West Virginia. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) The Seal of Civic Literacy shall not replace or alter any existing graduation requirements.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;18-36-5. Administration and Implementation.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) The Department shall: </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Develop the design, format, and official insignia of the Seal of Civic Literacy; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Establish uniform procedures for verifying student eligibility and awarding the seal; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Provide guidance to county boards of education and public charter schools regarding implementation; and </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Ensure that the seal is awarded consistently and fairly across all public schools in the state. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) County boards of education and public charter schools shall: </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Identify students who meet the requirements of this article; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Submit verification of eligible students to the Department in a manner prescribed by the Department; and </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Ensure that eligible students receive recognition of the Seal of Civic Literacy prior to or at graduation. </span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;18-36-6. Recognition and Use of the Seal.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) A student awarded the Seal of Civic Literacy may: </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Include the seal as an academic honor on college, scholarship, military, or employment applications; and </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Be recognized at graduation ceremonies, awards programs, or other academic events. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) The Department is encouraged to: </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Promote awareness of the Seal of Civic Literacy among institutions of higher education, employers, and scholarship organizations; and </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Publicly recognize schools that demonstrate strong participation and achievement in civic education. </span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;18-36-7. Rulemaking Authority. </span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">The State Board of Education may promulgate rules in accordance with applicable provisions of state law as necessary to implement the provisions of this article.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;18-36-8. Costs and Funding.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) The Seal of Civic Literacy shall be implemented using existing resources of the Department to the greatest extent practicable. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) The seal may consist of a printed certificate, diploma sticker, transcript notation, or any combination thereof, as determined by the Department. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) Additional costs associated with the design, printing, or distribution of the seal shall be minimized and may be funded through: </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Existing appropriations; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Partnerships with nonprofit civic education organizations; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Private donations; </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Grants available for civics education initiatives; or </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(5) Federal or state competitive education funds, where permissible by law. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) Nothing in this section shall require county boards of education or public charter schools to incur significant new costs.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;18-36-9. Severability.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">If any provision of this article or its application to any person or circumstance is held invalid, such invalidity shall not affect other provisions or applications of the article that can be given effect without the invalid provision or application, and to this end the provisions of this article are declared to be severable. </span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;18-36-10. Effective Date. </span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">This article shall take effect on July 1 following its passage and approval.</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to provide for the creation of the West Virginia Seal of Civic Literacy Act.</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added.</span></p>


